The Calf is a very beautiful and peaceful place, with fantastic views over the sea, beautiful coastline, 3 lighthouses and lots of seabirds.
Day trips leave from Port Erin.

It is possible to stay overnight on the Calf of Man during the summer months. You may contact the Manx Museum for a permit in advance. The farmhouse is used by the Warden, but has a couple of spare rooms. Water and electricity are limited, and you must be prepared to take your own food.
